HEADWORD: Unsister
<hw>Un*sis"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sister</ets>.]</ety> <def>To separate, as sisters;
to disjoin.</def> <mark>[Poetic & R.]</mark>
